buildStopPersistentChannel

public static OutMessage buildStopPersistentChannel(java.lang.String jmfUrl,
                                                    java.lang.String queueEntryId,
                                                    java.lang.String jobId)
Builds a JMF message containing a StopPersistentChannel command. If the parameters queueEntryId or jobId are specified a StopPersistentChannel command is created for stopping subscriptions for the specified job.

Parameters:
jmfUrl - the JMF URL owning the subscription (/JMF/Command/StopPersChParams/@URL)
queueEntryId - the QueueEntryID of the job to stop the subscription for; null to stop all subscriptiosn to the JMF URL
jobId - the JobID of the job to stop the subscription for; null to stop all subscriptions to the JMF URL
Returns:
